It makes great for me every day

This Pizza Place is on Livingston Street in Downtown Brooklyn right next to Cookies Department Stores and down the street from IHOP and the Goodwill Store check it out if your in the area for a quick snack, lunch or dinner and the price is budget friendly 🍕🍕🍕
Price was great & The owners was nice every time i have lunch there thank you
#BEST PIZZA;  #BEST 0.99C; BEST HOT PIZZ W/BUBBLING CHEESE In Down Town BKLYN. Always fresh and delicious.....😊😍😋🤩
Regular pizza. Nothing extraordinary. Customer service could be better. A quick fix.
Great pizza for 1.00, clean place but not enough chair or tables to stay and eat.
Dollar pizza that tastes great! Its brooklyn fagetaboutit!

Pizza be coming right out the oven and still be cold. Pizza could be a bit thicker. I do however like that they went back to charging $1. Keeping the tradition going with that $1 price
My first time having $1 slice pizza & it was good!!!

(Translated by Google) The place looks dirty (grease on the walls and ceiling) but the hygiene looked impeccable for the food. The employees washed their hands several times, that's worth noting. In terms of food, we know what we're going for: a 2-part + 1 drink formula for $ 2.75 typically American. For a more European formula, it amounts to $ 16 a gigantic pizza + 2 drinks for 2 people. No toilet.  (Original) L'endroit semble sale (graisse sur les murs et au plafond) mais l'hygiène avait l'air impec pour la nourriture. Les employés se sont lavées les mains plusieurs fois, c'est à noter. Pour ce qui est de la nourriture, on sait pour quoi on y va : une formule à 2 parts + 1 boisson pour 2.75 $ typiquement américaine. Pour une formule plus européenne, ça revient à 16 $ une pizza gigantesque + 2 boissons pour 2 personnes. Pas de toilettes.
They're pizzai is delicious. My Family loves it.
I actually lost my wallet at this pizza shop, but the counter guy was very helpful and cooperative by showing me the surveillance video of what happened.
The pizza is good and its only a dollar a slice.
Pizza is great..... Place is kind of dirty
Simply loved it. Hot, fresh, tasty, & cheap! Go for it ..no regrets.
Loved it need one in Harlem guys.EveryimeI come I come to Brooklyn it's a must!
Good tasting pizza on the Cheap, I recommend it when You want a nice bite.
best dollar pizza next to brooklyn campuses! better than most pizza spots chagering 2+ you need to try t least once if you're in the area

Amazing pizza for a cheap price. Would definitely recommend.
Nothing like a cheap slice on the run. Will visit again on Fulton street Brooklyn NYC.

Good slice of pizza for a buck

Cheap, fresh and fast. I only buy the plain slices. The only thing is that the crust sometimes they cut the slices smaller than they should be.

(Translated by Google) Tasty AF  (Original) Tasty AF

A quick bit to eat. Simple slice, garlic powder, and grape soda to finish it off. The slices are not bad. I've had the vegetable slice on occasion which can be filling. However, for a quick slice it is enjoyable. You may want to ask them to warm it up a bit more though as they can get busy and give up a slice that is not hot enough.

It's $1 pizza, it's bad pizza... really bad that I rather have frozen. The bread doesn't taste close to pizza dough and the sauce is closer to ketchup than tomato sauce and the cheese is probably the closest thing to pizza. but hey for $1 you get a slice. There are way better $1 pizza joints in Manhattan but if you're here and craving cheap eat I guess it's better than starving

(Translated by Google) Simple, fast and cheap. The 99c cheese pizza is no big deal, but it saves you if you're hungry between meals. Instead the $ 1.5 meat patty is quite good and quite filling. The other pizzas, with more ingredients, are worth between $ 2-4 and look good, although I haven't tried them.  (Original) Sencillo, rápido y barato. La pizza de 99c de queso no es nada del otro mundo, pero te salva si tienes hambre entre horas. En cambio la empanada de carne de 1,5$ está bastante bien y es bastante contundente. Las demás pizzas, con más ingredientes, valen entre 2-4 dólares y tienen buena pinta, aunque no las he probado.
One of my favorite places in NY. Cheap good pizza, $2.75 for 2 slices & a can. Good quick bite.

Idiots can never open on time...seems like they work only whenever they want! I'm talking about them already being inside but just refuse to open the doors until...they feel like it. Just another inefficient incompetent small business richly deserving of being pushed out by ever-increasing gentrification!! And I say this as someone who's once tipped $5 here just to help cheer up a sad-sack lookin' worker. Obviously, the other guy, a smart-alecky tall kid with glasses is the owner's son 'cause he acts way too casual and amused for someone actually concerns about earning money....
